der Nazi rule. German as a Jewish Problem tells the Jewish history of the German language, focusing on Jewish national movements in Central and Eastern Europe and Palestine/Israel. Marc Volovici considers key writers and activists whose work reflected the multilingual nature of the Jewish national sphere and the centrality of the German language within it, and argues that it is impossible to understand the histories of modern Hebrew and Yiddish without situating them in relation to German. This book offers a new understanding of the language problem in modern Jewish history, turning to German to illuminate the questions and dilemmas that largely defined the experience of European Jews in the age of nationalism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aGerman languagexHistory. 0aJewish scholarszGermanyxHistory. 0aJewsxCultural assimilationzGermany. 0aJewszGermanyxIdentity. 0aJewszGermanyxLanguages. 7aHISTORY / Jewish.2bisacsh  aGerman.  aGermany.  aHebrew.  aIdeology.  aLanguage.  aMultilingualism.  aNationalism.  aPalestine.  aYiddish.  aZionism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020 Englishz978311070477808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020z9783110704570oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069218140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150361310240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503613102423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503613102.jpg  a978-3-11-069218-1  SUP Frontlist eBook-